			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hey all,
<br />

<br />
     This is my first post at the Runes, but I've been a viewer of this web site for as long as I can remember. I played a chanter on Trov for 3 years and then went to FFXI for 1 year to bridge the gap from EQ1 >> EQ2.
<br />

<br />
So I'm here too see what you all think of Charm, your tricks, strategies, solo tactics ect. I recently hit lvl 40 as a Coercer and have been using it for the past few levels and I'm here to submit my review. First off I'm happy to say that when they tell you it can only be used on lesser mobs it dosen't mean you cant charm Red con's. What it means is that you cannot charm ^^ or ^^^ mobs, even a grey ^^ will give you the message "Target is too powerful" however I've had much success in charming Red single up arrow cons providing the spell isn't resisted. I also find that the spell works best in a group enviroment due to the way most encounters in EQ2 are multi enemy battles and when charm breaks (about every 15-20 sec) you have a tank to take the blows. I find that when using it in a group however you should always buff your tank with Annoying Demeanor because a broken charm usually generates large aggro and this buff dose the job of making the mob run back to the tank instead of directly at you, and it seems if you have any mezzes currently active they all break when you land charm on a non-mezzed mob, so be sure your not charming during a named fight where mezz is most important. I found that the spell is certain death when used solo and ill tell you why.. First the charmed pet dose not taunt, second I think the spell is rigged never to land for more then a fraction of a second on the first cast forcing you to take blows until it's reuse timer is up and 8 sec is a long time when you being hit and interrupted trying to get off a root, stun or mezz. I've tried Charm on everything from a fallen orc outside FP in commons.. to the NB's in rivervale, and my rigged theory hasn't failed me once, never holds 1st cast.. but I found a little trick that seems to counter this problem, If you cast another spell on the mob such as Root or Haruspex (a spell that will not be cancelled out by charm) before casting the charm spell then charm will not break until the duration of the 1st spell cast on the mob ends. So what I do in a group is cast Forced Hesitation followed immediately by Beguile and then my charm will hold until the reuse timer is ready and I can recast it quickly only suffering 1 blow from the mob usually. Then once you've gotten past the 1st cast hump you can use the mob for the rest of the fight flawlessly. Currently I'm fighting Nightbloods in Rivervale and they come in encounters of A ^^ Shadowrage and A ^ Harrower, I always tell the tank to kill the shadowrage 1st so I can charm the Harrower, the result is amazing as long as you use the above strategy. These Harrower pets cant be out damaged by any class, they hit costantly for between 450 - 1000 <img src="images/smiles/boxer.gif" alt="Boxer" border="0" /> , well.. I've been trying to break 1k, the highest hit I've had was 991 and thats still amazing ! Rangers and Assassins have a hard time breaking 600 damage with their most powerful attacks and this pet hits over 600 on a regular basis. 
<br />

<br />
So now that I've broke the cherry on charm lets all submit our stories.. and see if there are some more tricks that can help use this spell solo, like one that will keep the mobs aggro'd on each other rather then you. I've been thinking of a few that I still want to try.. such as on an encounter of 2 single up arrow mobs, opening with AoE mezz.. then root both, then charm 1.. maybe?? Still lots of work to do here, but all I can tell you is that Charm is the most fun I've ever had with my coercer and I'm glad as ever that I didn't go Illusionist.
<br />

<br />
PS, Forgot to say that the charmed mob cannot be buffed or recharmed until charm wears off because you get the message "Target not grouped" and it cant be debuffed, nuked or rooted ect. while charmed because you get the message "Target not an enemy". 
<br />

<br />
Thank you
<br />
Kothar Magistic - lvl 40 Coercer - Befallen</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
