			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just got to 37 and a half the other day and have one night of fiddling with charm now.  Not sure if it's changed from when this post started but hell...everything keeps changing anyway.
<br />

<br />
First...charm does not resist on first cast all the time.  Sometimes it does and then you have a pissed off mob on you, but most of the time I found I had a nice pet.
<br />

<br />
Charm only lasts maximum 36 seconds.  You can't reapply charm to extend that...it will not let you cast a negative spell on a friendly.  It does seem they can resist charm earlier randomly though.  
<br />

<br />
When it wears off, if the mob is non-aggro to you, or you are out of aggro range for a KOS mob, you won't have aggro.  I like this...means that I don't have TWO pissed off mobs on me then.  
<br />

<br />
36 seconds doesn't seem like much but I've found it does make a huge diff in damage output...especially if you find a good high DPS pet.  Still experimenting with that though.<br />_________________<br />Ootpek Ubiqitous
<br />
ERTW!!! Enchanters Rule the World!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
