			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok...so they changed charm again.  Now it WILL aggro after it wears off.  So forget what I posted above about that.  
<br />

<br />
One thing I did find out, by accident cause of bad targetting with similar mobs...is that you CAN CHARM MULTIPLE mobs.  
<br />

<br />
So...with a 2 second cast time, 8 second recast, and 36 second duration you can almost keep 3 mobs completly charmed and 2 is easy to do.  This is AWESOME DPS although I would only recommend you do it within a group situation as solo you have too much trouble with interrupts and recharming to live long.  
<br />

<br />
Typical way I worked this is let the MT build up a little aggro then start charming the mobs he's NOT on.  10 seconds later you should have 2 pets on his target and it should be dying FAST.  When charm breaks...he should still have aggro allowing for easy recharming or to let him take the mob off your hands.  Long fights with lots of recharming will earn you enough aggro eventually that you have to take some beats though.
<br />

<br />
Try this and enjoy!<br />_________________<br />Ootpek Ubiqitous
<br />
ERTW!!! Enchanters Rule the World!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
